  "body": "When calling `EngineForkChoiceUpdatedV1` w/ a `req: EngingeForkChoiceUpdatedRequest.PayloadAttributes{PrevRandao:0x0,SuggestedFeeRecipient:0x0}`, erigon gives the error: `\"rpc error: code = Internal dec = runtime error: invalid memory reference or nil pointer dereference`. \r\n\r\nHere's the PayloadAttributes GRPS spec:\r\n```\r\nPayloadAttributes *EnginePayloadAttributes `protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=payloadAttributes,proto3\" json:\"payloadAttributes,omitempty\"`\r\n}\r\n```\r\nhttps://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon-lib/blob/4b0ff0ae5e26e17b1d14fdb36aa7f27a1e56bae4/gointerfaces/remote/ethbackend.pb.go#L632\r\n\r\nIt's specifically these two lines that cause the memory error: \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/5c5094ae6af74f775c397726ab4b0136c47200a7/ethdb/privateapi/ethbackend.go#L590-L591\r\n\r\nIt seems like there's a better way to fail here. It took me a bit of time to track this one down. Then again, maybe \"don't call the function w/ 0 value arguments\" is the correct solution.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
